1
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:23,500
英文字幕从www.AllSubs.org下载
新浪微博@蓝色风暴911 原创翻译

2
00:03:45,035 --> 00:03:46,764
Yes, sir. I will do that.

是的，先生。我会去做！

3
00:04:06,090 --> 00:04:08,285
Urgent. Urgent.

紧急。紧急。

4
00:04:08,325 --> 00:04:10,520
Where's Lin? Lin Braddock?

林在哪里？林・巴洛克？

5
00:04:10,561 --> 00:04:11,528
She left.

她离开了。

6
00:04:11,562 --> 00:04:12,529
You know where she went?

你知道她去哪儿了吗？

7
00:04:12,563 --> 00:04:13,791
I don't know.

我不知道。

8
00:04:19,436 --> 00:04:20,835
Lin...

林...

9
00:04:20,871 --> 00:04:23,066
is your man really take you to America?

你的男人真的会带你去美国吗？

10
00:04:23,107 --> 00:04:25,302
Yes, of course.

是的，当然。

11
00:04:33,550 --> 00:04:35,040
What about all this?

这些怎么办？

12
00:04:35,919 --> 00:04:37,750
I can't take everything.

我不能带上所有东西。

13
00:05:10,688 --> 00:05:11,950
What about this?

这个呢？

14
00:05:12,690 --> 00:05:13,657
Yes. Take it.

是的，带上。

15
00:05:13,691 --> 00:05:15,352
Take anything you want.

带上任何你想要的东西。

16
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:19,358
Stay back! Stay back!

退后！退后！

17
00:05:19,396 --> 00:05:20,829
I can't let you in!

我不能让你进去！

18
00:05:21,565 --> 00:05:22,998
Please disperse.

请散开。

19
00:05:23,734 --> 00:05:25,361
We can't help you all.

我们不能帮助你们所有人。

20
00:05:25,402 --> 00:05:27,029
We have no room!

我们没有房间！

21
00:05:27,071 --> 00:05:29,266
Captain, has a Lin Braddock
come through the gate?

队长，有没有一个叫林・巴洛克的人通过大门？

22
00:05:29,306 --> 00:05:33,003
If you work for the Embassy,
have your papers ready!

如果你为大使馆工作，准备好你的证件！

23
00:05:37,614 --> 00:05:38,638
Not yet, Colonel.

没有，上校。

24
00:05:38,682 --> 00:05:39,876
You're a friend of Lin?

你是林的一个朋友？

25
00:05:39,917 --> 00:05:40,941
I'm her husband.

我是她的丈夫。

26
00:05:40,984 --> 00:05:42,474
She went to her home.

她去自己家了。

27
00:05:42,519 --> 00:05:43,645
When?

什么时候？

28
00:05:43,687 --> 00:05:45,086
One hour, maybe two.

一个小时前，也许两个。

29
00:05:45,122 --> 00:05:47,113
She had to get her papers.

她必须拿到自己的证件。

30
00:05:47,157 --> 00:05:49,182
Please disperse!

请散开！

31
00:05:55,399 --> 00:05:57,458
The dress is so beautiful.

这件礼服真漂亮。

32
00:05:57,501 --> 00:05:58,934
Thank you.

谢谢。

33
00:06:01,038 --> 00:06:03,666
Good-bye, Min. Take care.

再见，敏。保重。

34
00:06:03,707 --> 00:06:04,696
Bye.

再见。

35
00:07:55,953 --> 00:07:57,011
Hold it.

且慢。

36
00:07:57,054 --> 00:07:59,215
We found her upstairs.You know her?

我们在楼上找到她。你认识她？

37
00:08:58,115 --> 00:09:00,310
Guess what I've got.

猜猜我得到了什么。

38
00:10:21,732 --> 00:10:22,699
All right. Hit it.

好吧。炸了它。

39
00:10:22,733 --> 00:10:26,722
Roger.

明白。
【全称：I have received all the last message。
其中R是RECEIVE，O是ALL，GER就是MESSAGE，
这个词是由WW2(二战)的时候开始使用的。】

40
00:10:27,871 --> 00:10:29,964
I said get the hell off of there!

我说过离开那个鬼地方！

41
00:10:37,481 --> 00:10:39,779
I'm Lin Braddock!

我是林・巴洛克！

42
00:10:39,816 --> 00:10:41,374
Look at the list!

看看这个表格！

43
00:10:41,418 --> 00:10:43,909
I work for the Embassy!

我为大使馆工作！

44
00:10:43,954 --> 00:10:45,216
Lin Braddock!

林・巴洛克！

45
00:10:45,255 --> 00:10:46,222
Captain!

队长！

46
00:10:46,256 --> 00:10:47,223
What is it?

什么事？

47
00:10:47,257 --> 00:10:48,918
She says she's on the list.

她说她在表格上。

48
00:10:48,959 --> 00:10:49,926
What name?

什么名字？

49
00:10:49,960 --> 00:10:51,052
Lin Braddock!

林・巴洛克！

50
00:10:51,094 --> 00:10:53,654
I'm a translator for the embassy!

我是一名大使馆的翻译！

51
00:10:53,697 --> 00:10:54,664
Give me your papers.

把你的证件给我。

52
00:10:54,698 --> 00:10:57,030
I lost them!They stole it!

我把它们弄丢了！他们偷走了！

53
00:10:57,067 --> 00:10:58,762
Please! Look at the list!

拜托了！看看这个表格！

54
00:10:58,802 --> 00:11:00,633
I need your papers!

我需要你的证件！

55
00:11:00,670 --> 00:11:03,434
I told you! Somebody stole them!

我刚告诉过你，有人把证件偷走了！

56
00:11:03,473 --> 00:11:04,667
Oh, God! You have to believe me!

哦，上帝!你必须相信我！

57
00:11:04,708 --> 00:11:06,733
Well, there's nothing I can do about that.

额，那我没有办法。

58
00:11:06,777 --> 00:11:09,541
Please! Lin! Look at the list!

拜托了！林！看看这个表格！

59
00:11:09,579 --> 00:11:10,705
This morning there was a Colonel Braddock.

今天早上那里是有一个巴洛克上校。

60
00:11:10,747 --> 00:11:12,078
Is Colonel Braddock your husband?

巴洛克上校是你的丈夫？

61
00:11:12,115 --> 00:11:13,104
Yes! Yes!

是的！是的！

62
00:11:22,125 --> 00:11:25,185
For crying out loud! These people are crazy!

搞什么名堂！这些人都疯了！

63
00:11:25,228 --> 00:11:26,752
Get them down!

把他们放倒！

64
00:11:26,797 --> 00:11:28,822
Shoot them! Get it together!

向他们射击！都集中起来！

65
00:11:35,505 --> 00:11:37,473
Grab the seal.

抓住标志。

66
00:11:40,444 --> 00:11:42,207
Step aside! Move!

让开！走开！

67
00:11:43,847 --> 00:11:45,872
Come on, Junior.Get these folks out!

加油，晚辈。把这些人赶出去！

68
00:11:50,253 --> 00:11:52,153
Get off me!Get out of the way!

离开我！把路让开！

69
00:11:53,190 --> 00:11:54,714
Move! Stand aside!

走开！靠边站！

70
00:12:02,799 --> 00:12:03,857
Let's go!

我们走！

71
00:12:08,572 --> 00:12:10,836
Please!

拜托！

72
00:12:12,976 --> 00:12:15,206
Wait! Please!

等等！拜托！

73
00:12:15,245 --> 00:12:17,372
Please!

拜托！

74
00:12:38,935 --> 00:12:39,959
Commander, please.

指挥官，拜托。

75
00:12:40,003 --> 00:12:40,992
I give you a thousand dollar.

我给你一千美元。

76
00:12:41,037 --> 00:12:43,972
Please. I love America.Come on.

拜托。我热爱美国。来吧。

77
00:12:44,007 --> 00:12:44,996
Hey.

嘿。

78
00:12:45,709 --> 00:12:46,801
Let me go up.

让我上去。

79
00:12:57,354 --> 00:12:58,343
Let me go!

让我走！

80
00:13:01,358 --> 00:13:03,383
OK. Take off.
好吧。起飞。

81
00:13:04,427 --> 00:13:05,894
Son of a bitch!

婊子养的！【王八蛋】

82
00:13:11,067 --> 00:13:13,001
Don't worry.We got you, Colonel!

别担心。我们抓住你了，上校！

83
00:13:13,036 --> 00:13:14,196
That bastard was probably V.C.
那杂种可能是副主席。

84
00:13:14,237 --> 00:13:16,205
All right.There you go, Colonel.

好吧。就这样，上校。

85
00:13:17,507 --> 00:13:18,906
All right.Move them out. Move!

好了。快把他们运出去。快走！

86
00:13:30,153 --> 00:13:34,214
No medals, no ribbons

没有奖牌，没有丝带

87
00:13:34,257 --> 00:13:36,987
No welcome parade

没有欢迎游行

88
00:13:37,027 --> 00:13:40,224
It's a lonely road home

这是一条孤独的回家路

89
00:13:40,263 --> 00:13:44,962
And a heavy price to pay

和一个沉重的代价

90
00:13:48,772 --> 00:13:52,401
Now I say a prayer

现在我做一次祈祷

91
00:13:52,442 --> 00:13:55,275
For those that remain

为了那些留在这里的人

92
00:13:55,312 --> 00:13:57,212
And I wonder

并且我怀疑

93
00:13:57,247 --> 00:14:04,983
Will they ever find freedom again?

他们还会再一次找到自由吗？

94
00:14:23,807 --> 00:14:25,399
- Hi, Cindy. - Hey.

- 嗨，辛迪。- 嘿。

95
00:14:25,442 --> 00:14:27,774
I should run for president.

我要竞选总统。

96
00:14:27,811 --> 00:14:28,778
What'd you say?

你刚说什么？

97
00:14:28,812 --> 00:14:29,801
I didn't think he needed to.

我不认为他需要。

98
00:14:29,846 --> 00:14:30,972
Oh, really?

哦，真的？

99
00:14:54,004 --> 00:14:55,130
Mr. Braddock?

巴洛克先生？

100
00:14:56,206 --> 00:14:57,173
That's right.

正是。

101
00:14:57,207 --> 00:14:59,334
Colonel James Braddock?

詹姆斯・巴洛克上校？

102
00:15:01,745 --> 00:15:02,712
What can I do for you?

我能为你做些什么？

103
00:15:02,746 --> 00:15:05,078
Could I have a few moments of your time?

我可以打扰你一些时间吗？

104
00:15:07,417 --> 00:15:08,816
- Sit down.- Thank you.

- 请坐。- 谢谢。

105
00:15:13,723 --> 00:15:15,020
Please, uh...

拜托，额...

106
00:15:15,058 --> 00:15:17,583
could we please talk more privately?

我们可以更加私密的交谈吗？

107
00:15:20,697 --> 00:15:22,324
Yeah. Sure.

是的。当然。

108
00:15:22,365 --> 00:15:23,559
Thank you.

谢谢。

109
00:15:38,615 --> 00:15:40,549
Would you like something to drink?

你需要喝点什么吗？

110
00:15:40,583 --> 00:15:41,845
No, no. Thank you.

不，不需要。谢谢。

111
00:15:41,885 --> 00:15:43,546
I am Reverend Polanski...

我是波兰斯基牧师...

112
00:15:43,586 --> 00:15:46,749
from the Amerasian Children's
Mission in Vietnam.

来自越南的美亚混血儿童教会。【慈善机构】

113
00:15:46,790 --> 00:15:48,087
Occasionally,
I come to this country...

偶尔，我回到这个国家...

114
00:15:48,124 --> 00:15:49,955
to raise funds for the mission.

为了教会筹集资金。

115
00:15:50,493 --> 00:15:52,654
I was hoping I could find you before I went back.

我一直希望能在回去之前找到你。

116
00:15:52,696 --> 00:15:54,994
Find me? Why?

找到我？为什么？

117
00:15:55,031 --> 00:15:58,933
About a year ago,
a young Amerasian child...

大约一年之前,一个年幼的美亚混血儿童...

118
00:15:58,968 --> 00:16:02,165
came to the mission
begging for help.


来到教会乞求帮助。

119
00:16:02,205 --> 00:16:04,639
He told me that his mother was sick.

他告诉我说他的妈妈生病了。

120
00:16:04,674 --> 00:16:06,505
I went to see if there was anything I could do...

我过去探望有什么事情自己可以帮忙...

121
00:16:06,543 --> 00:16:09,205
and found out she worked for the U.S. Embassy...

并且发现她曾经为美国大使馆工作...

122
00:16:09,245 --> 00:16:10,610
during the war.

是在越战期间。

123
00:16:10,647 --> 00:16:15,209
She has been severely punished by the Vietnamese government.

她已经被越南政府严厉地惩罚。

124
00:16:15,251 --> 00:16:17,219
Having the half-American son has made things...

有一个半美国血统的儿子让事情变得...

125
00:16:17,253 --> 00:16:18,220
even worse for her.

对她而言更加糟糕。

126
00:16:18,254 --> 00:16:20,415
I'm sorry to hear that, but...

听到这些我很伤心，但是...

127
00:16:21,157 --> 00:16:22,522
what's that got to do with me?

那和我有什么关系？

128
00:16:22,559 --> 00:16:27,792
The woman's married name is Mrs. James Braddock.

这位女士的已婚名字是詹姆斯・巴洛克夫人。

129
00:16:27,831 --> 00:16:29,423
What did you say?

你说什么？

130
00:16:29,466 --> 00:16:31,764
I'm talking about your wife, Mr. Braddock.

我正在谈论你的妻子，巴洛克先生。

131
00:16:31,801 --> 00:16:32,768
Lin Tan Cang.

林昙苍。

132
00:16:32,802 --> 00:16:34,497
You're mistaken.

你搞错了。

133
00:16:34,537 --> 00:16:36,334
No. There is no mistake.

不，没有搞错。

134
00:16:36,373 --> 00:16:38,568
My wife died during the fall of Saigon.

我的妻子在西贡沦陷时牺牲了。

135
00:16:38,608 --> 00:16:41,406
Your wife is alive.I know her quite well.

你的妻子还活着。我知道她很好。

136
00:16:41,444 --> 00:16:42,911
Your son's name is Van.

你儿子的名字叫凡。

137
00:16:42,946 --> 00:16:44,413
He's now 12 years old.

他现在12岁。

138
00:16:44,447 --> 00:16:46,472
My wife and I didn't have a son.

我的妻子和我没有生下儿子。

139
00:16:46,516 --> 00:16:49,610
Why is it so hard for you to believe me?

为什么对你来说相信我是如此的艰难？

140
00:16:49,652 --> 00:16:52,587
Because I saw my wife's body burned to a crisp, that's why.

因为我看到自己妻子的尸体都烧焦了，这就是原因。

141
00:16:52,622 --> 00:16:54,214
You may have seen a body...

你可能看到过一具尸体...

142
00:16:54,257 --> 00:16:55,485
but it wasn't your wife.

但那不是你的妻子。

143
00:16:55,525 --> 00:16:57,288
Lin Tan Cang is alive!

林昙苍还活着！

144
00:16:59,896 --> 00:17:01,488
Believe whatever you want, Reverend.

坚信你所想要的一切，牧师。

145
00:17:01,531 --> 00:17:03,761
I know better.

我很清楚。

146
00:17:03,800 --> 00:17:05,825
Your few moments are up.

给你的一些时间结束了。

147
00:17:13,610 --> 00:17:16,545
Oh, they had this great
place in Georgetown.

哦，他们在乔治敦有这个伟大的地方。

148
00:17:16,579 --> 00:17:18,274
Really nice.

真的不错。

149
00:17:19,115 --> 00:17:21,345
Yeah, of course.
I saw it last week.

是的，当然。我上星期刚见过它。

150
00:17:21,384 --> 00:17:22,817
Even if you did believe me...

即使你相信我...

151
00:17:22,852 --> 00:17:25,878
I doubt if there
is anything you could do.

我也怀疑你是否能去做些什么。

152
00:17:25,922 --> 00:17:27,514
I've already gone
to the State Department...

我已经去过国务院...

153
00:17:27,557 --> 00:17:29,149
and they will do nothing...

并且他们什么也不会去做...

154
00:17:29,959 --> 00:17:31,790
but I had to let you know.

但我必须让你知道。

155
00:17:33,229 --> 00:17:35,424
Good-bye, Mr. Braddock.

再见，巴洛克先生。

156
00:17:35,465 --> 00:17:37,126
God be with you.

上帝与你同在。

157
00:18:01,591 --> 00:18:02,717
Braddock?

巴洛克？

158
00:18:03,793 --> 00:18:04,953
C.I.A.

中央情报局

159
00:18:06,563 --> 00:18:07,825
Please come with us.

请跟我们来。

160
00:18:48,304 --> 00:18:50,534
Wait outside.

在外面等着。

161
00:18:53,743 --> 00:18:56,735
It's been a long time,
Colonel Braddock.

很久不见了，巴洛克上校。

162
00:18:56,779 --> 00:18:58,440
How have you been?

你过得如何？

163
00:18:58,481 --> 00:19:00,608
You know how I've
been, Littlejohn.

你知道我过得怎么样，小约翰。

164
00:19:02,418 --> 00:19:04,477
Now, what do you want?

现在，你想要什么？

165
00:19:04,521 --> 00:19:07,684
You just met with
a Reverend Polanski.

你刚刚会见了一个叫波兰斯基的牧师。

166
00:19:07,724 --> 00:19:08,691
So?

如何？

167
00:19:08,725 --> 00:19:10,852
Did he tell you
some kind of...

他有没有告诉你那种...

168
00:19:10,894 --> 00:19:14,762
crazy story about
your wife being alive?

关于你妻子还活着的疯狂故事？

169
00:19:19,502 --> 00:19:20,696
Is it a crazy story?

这是一个疯狂的故事？

170
00:19:20,737 --> 00:19:22,602
Of course it is.

当然是。

171
00:19:30,413 --> 00:19:32,643
Big mistake, Littlejohn.

大错误，小约翰。

172
00:19:35,318 --> 00:19:37,252
I didn't believe it until now.

直到现在我都无法相信这件事。

173
00:19:40,623 --> 00:19:42,682
What are you going to do
about getting them out?

为了救他们出来，你将会怎么做？

174
00:19:45,461 --> 00:19:46,723
Nothing.

什么都不做。

175
00:19:46,763 --> 00:19:48,492
If I don't get them out...

如果我不把他们救出来...

176
00:19:49,465 --> 00:19:50,830
they're going to die.

他们将会死去。

177
00:19:52,569 --> 00:19:55,436
People die every day.

每天都有人死亡。

178
00:19:59,509 --> 00:20:00,806
Braddock!

巴洛克！

179
00:20:00,843 --> 00:20:02,902
I'm warning you.

我警告你。

180
00:20:02,946 --> 00:20:05,380
Don't step on any toes.

别踩到任何脚趾。【别得罪任何人。】

181
00:20:11,020 --> 00:20:13,284
I don't step on toes,
Littlejohn.

我不会踩到脚趾,小约翰。

182
00:20:15,058 --> 00:20:17,253
I step on necks.

我踩到脖子上。
【不仅得罪，还要惩罚。】

183
00:20:40,083 --> 00:20:42,142
Welcome to Bangkok.

欢迎来到曼谷。【泰国首都】

184
00:20:42,185 --> 00:20:43,550
We hope you enjoyed
your flight...

我们希望您享受这次飞行之旅...

185
00:20:43,586 --> 00:20:45,884
and will fly
with Thai Airlines again.

并再次乘坐泰国航空公司的飞机。

186
00:20:58,234 --> 00:20:59,599
Take me downtown.

带我去市中心。

187
00:21:11,180 --> 00:21:12,169
40 bob, please.

请支付40块。

188
00:21:30,433 --> 00:21:31,525
Now, look here, mate.

现在，看这里，伴侣。

189
00:21:31,567 --> 00:21:33,125
I said I need more room.

我说过我需要更多房间。

190
00:21:33,169 --> 00:21:34,227
Now beat it!

现在打它！

191
00:21:42,679 --> 00:21:44,977
Whoo! You take me home.

呼！你带我回家。

192
00:21:47,316 --> 00:21:48,874
You want to try knocking me off?

你想试试击倒我吗？

193
00:21:50,186 --> 00:21:52,017
How the hell are you, Braddock?

你怎么样，巴洛克？

194
00:21:52,055 --> 00:21:53,955
Did you get everything?

你一切都准备好了吗？

195
00:21:56,325 --> 00:21:57,792
Yes, I got everything...

是的，一切都有了...

196
00:21:57,827 --> 00:22:00,057
but it sure as hell wasn't easy.

但肯定是非常不容易。

197
00:22:00,096 --> 00:22:02,360
That's why
I appreciate you, Mik.

这就是我欣赏你的原因，米克。

198
00:22:02,398 --> 00:22:04,866
That's what friends
are for, Braddock...

这就是朋友的作用，巴洛克...

199
00:22:05,368 --> 00:22:06,392
which reminds me.

我想起来了。

200
00:22:06,436 --> 00:22:07,596
Got my money?

我的钱带来了吗？

201
00:22:16,446 --> 00:22:17,413
Let's go.

我们走。

202
00:22:17,447 --> 00:22:19,278
No, no, no!
No need to hurry.

不，不，不！不要急。

203
00:22:19,816 --> 00:22:21,443
The plane won't be loaded
for several hours yet.

几个小时之内飞机还不会降落。

204
00:22:21,484 --> 00:22:23,452
We got a long drive out of town.

我们需要很长一段驾驶开出城市。

205
00:22:26,456 --> 00:22:28,822
Oh, shit. Here comes trouble.

哦，见鬼。麻烦来了。

206
00:22:31,928 --> 00:22:33,486
Go get the car
and pull out front.

去把汽车开到前面来。

207
00:22:33,529 --> 00:22:35,053
Ah, OK.

啊，好的。

208
00:22:36,866 --> 00:22:37,833
Hey.

嘿。

209
00:22:37,867 --> 00:22:39,357
You're not going
anywhere, Miklachek.

你不能去任何地方，米克拉查克。

210
00:22:39,402 --> 00:22:40,426
Take him to the car.

把他带到汽车那边。

211
00:22:40,470 --> 00:22:42,495
Jeez. Hey, where's
the rules about...

老天。嘿，这是依据什么规则...

212
00:22:42,538 --> 00:22:44,096
Hey, watch my beer,
man! Hey, listen.

嘿，小心我的啤酒，老兄！嘿，听着。

213
00:22:44,140 --> 00:22:47,906
I warned you, Braddock,
not to fuck with us.

我警告你，巴洛克，别逼我们。

214
00:22:49,545 --> 00:22:51,445
Don't try to stop me,
Littlejohn.

不要尝试阻止我，小约翰。

215
00:22:51,481 --> 00:22:52,971
You're stopped.

你被阻止了。

216
00:22:53,015 --> 00:22:54,539
Come on.

来吧。

217
00:22:58,121 --> 00:23:00,214
Oh! Oh, my God!

哦！哦，我的天！

218
00:23:03,459 --> 00:23:05,654
Freeze, asshole,
or you're dead!

住手，混蛋，否则你死定了！

219
00:23:19,575 --> 00:23:21,042
Excuse me, girls.

对不起，姑娘们。

220
00:23:22,345 --> 00:23:23,369
Braddock!

巴洛克！

221
00:23:31,821 --> 00:23:32,879
Cut him off!

拦下他！

222
00:23:33,422 --> 00:23:34,582
Braddock!

巴洛克！

223
00:23:42,598 --> 00:23:43,587
Braddock.

巴洛克。

224
00:23:46,903 --> 00:23:48,928
Stop right there.

站在那别动！

225
00:23:57,246 --> 00:23:58,975
Braddock! Wait!

巴洛克！等等！

226
00:24:09,192 --> 00:24:10,557
Son of a bitch.

婊子养的。【王八蛋】

227
00:24:29,912 --> 00:24:31,106
You actually made it.

你真的成功了。

228
00:24:33,716 --> 00:24:34,705
- Shit! - Uh -oh.

- 娘的！-额 -哦。

229
00:24:39,755 --> 00:24:43,122
Braddock!
He's getting away!

巴洛克！他正在逃离！

230
00:24:43,159 --> 00:24:45,957
Hurry! Get in your cars!
Go after him! Hit it!

快点！进你们的车！跟着他！打它！

231
00:24:45,995 --> 00:24:48,190
Oh, no!

哦，不！

232
00:24:57,073 --> 00:24:59,132
Way to go, man!

做得好，伙计！
【That's the way to go. 的缩写，用来告诉一个人"他做得很好，请继续保持"。】

233
00:25:23,666 --> 00:25:25,463
Jesus, Braddock.

天啊【耶稣】，巴洛克。

234
00:25:26,068 --> 00:25:28,332
Couldn't you lighten up
just a teeny bit?

你就不能放松一点点？

235
00:25:28,371 --> 00:25:30,430
I mean, I got to live here.

我的意思是，我住在这里。

236
00:25:30,473 --> 00:25:32,737
You've got a one-way
ticket out.

你已经有出去的单程票了。

237
00:25:54,864 --> 00:25:56,627
Jesus, Braddock.

天啊，巴洛克。

238
00:25:57,400 --> 00:25:58,389
Watch it!

小心！

239
00:26:07,243 --> 00:26:08,676
Whoa!

哇哦！

240
00:26:36,272 --> 00:26:37,762
Oh, shit, Braddock.

哦，见鬼，巴洛克。

241
00:26:38,407 --> 00:26:42,207
We'll have the whole
damn police force after us.

我们会招来整个该死的警察局跟着。

242
00:26:42,244 --> 00:26:43,939
How far is it
to the plane?

到飞机还有多远？

243
00:26:43,980 --> 00:26:46,005
Uh, it's quite a ways
out of Bangkok.

额，出了曼谷还有相当一段路。

244
00:26:46,048 --> 00:26:48,915
No. It will be daylight
before we get there.

不。在我们到达之前就会天亮。

245
00:26:52,521 --> 00:26:53,852
Hey, the boss is coming!

嘿，老板来了！

246
00:26:58,260 --> 00:26:59,227
Don't hang around!

别整天闲逛！

247
00:26:59,261 --> 00:27:02,287
Why didn't you have
her going, man?

你们为什么不启动她，伙计？

248
00:27:04,300 --> 00:27:05,460
Let's go!

出发！

249
00:27:07,470 --> 00:27:09,199
Come, come, come!

来吧，来吧，来吧！

250
00:27:15,811 --> 00:27:17,540
Are you sure this thing
will get off the ground?

你确定这东西能飞上天？

251
00:27:17,580 --> 00:27:20,048
Oh, relax, mother.

哦，放松，老妈。

252
00:27:20,082 --> 00:27:22,550
Sit back. Enjoy the ride.

坐后面去。享受这次航行。

253
00:27:22,585 --> 00:27:24,382
It'll be just like Coney Island.

它将和康尼岛一样。

254
00:27:56,852 --> 00:27:59,480
OK, Braddock...

好吧，巴洛克...

255
00:27:59,522 --> 00:28:01,285
are you gonna tell me
where we're going now?

你现在想告诉我 我们要去哪里了吗？

256
00:28:01,323 --> 00:28:03,223
As if I didn't know.

我好像不知道。

257
00:28:03,926 --> 00:28:06,952
Along the coast.
Ganh Rai Bay.

沿着海岸。争莱湾。【西贡河出口】

258
00:28:10,833 --> 00:28:12,494
We're gonna have to
skim the waves...

看来我们必须掠过波浪...

259
00:28:12,535 --> 00:28:15,561
when we get there to
stay underneath their radar.

当我们到达那里就要保持在他们的雷达下面。

260
00:28:22,845 --> 00:28:25,245
Hey, Braddock, you've
done some flying.

嘿，巴洛克，你已经做过一些飞行了。

261
00:28:25,281 --> 00:28:27,215
Why don't you take
the controls, eh?

你为什么不来控制，额？

262
00:28:27,249 --> 00:28:28,477
Give me a rest.

让我休息一下。

263
00:28:29,185 --> 00:28:32,018
Let's see if you can fly
as well as you can drive, eh?

让我们瞧瞧你的飞行技术是否和你的驾车技术一样好，额？

264
00:28:32,054 --> 00:28:33,214
It's been a long time.

已经有一段时间了。

265
00:28:33,255 --> 00:28:34,449
Oh, you can do it.

哦，你可以做到的。

266
00:28:34,490 --> 00:28:35,889
I tell you...

我会告诉你...

267
00:28:35,925 --> 00:28:37,153
it's a lot calmer up here...

在这里平静的多...

268
00:28:37,193 --> 00:28:39,161
than it is in your automobile.
比起在你的汽车里。

269
00:28:46,402 --> 00:28:49,030
You know, when we get
to the drop zone...

你知道，当我们到达降落区...

270
00:28:49,071 --> 00:28:50,402
I'm gonna pull her
up into a climb...

我将会拉起她变成爬坡...

271
00:28:50,439 --> 00:28:51,770
and you'll have
about five seconds...

并且你只有5秒钟...

272
00:28:51,807 --> 00:28:54,275
to make the drop before
I put her into a dive.

在我把她变成俯冲之前来完成降落。

273
00:28:54,310 --> 00:28:55,743
I'll need ten seconds.

我需要10秒钟。

274
00:28:56,612 --> 00:28:58,807
Well, if you're a good boy,
I'll give you ten seconds.

好吧，如果你是个好男孩，我会给你10秒钟。

275
00:29:03,385 --> 00:29:05,785
Vietnam.

越南。

276
00:29:05,821 --> 00:29:08,221
I never thought
I'd be coming back.
我从没想过还会再回来。

277
00:29:08,257 --> 00:29:10,748
I guess we never really
can leave, can we?

我想我们从未真正能离开，能吗？

278
00:29:12,761 --> 00:29:13,750
Aw, come on.

嗷，加油。

279
00:29:13,796 --> 00:29:14,854
Get your ass back there.

到后面去。

280
00:29:14,897 --> 00:29:15,886
I'll take it.

我要执行了。

281
00:29:35,584 --> 00:29:36,573
OK, Braddock.

好吧，巴洛克。

282
00:29:36,619 --> 00:29:38,246
You got thirty seconds.

你有30秒。

283
00:29:51,133 --> 00:29:52,862
Good luck, mother.

好运，老妈。

284
00:30:11,387 --> 00:30:14,356
See you in hell,
you crazy bastard.

地狱里见，你这疯狂的混蛋。

285
00:31:21,690 --> 00:31:23,180
Come on!

来吧！

286
00:33:35,224 --> 00:33:38,352
Let us each give thanks
in our own way.

让我们各自用自己的方式来感恩。

287
00:33:47,102 --> 00:33:49,036
- Amen. - Amen.

- 阿门。-阿门。

288
00:33:53,976 --> 00:33:56,342
Thank you, Father,
wise and good...

谢谢你，上帝，聪明又善良...

289
00:33:56,378 --> 00:33:59,905
for home and friends
and daily food.

为了家庭、朋友们和日常的食物。

290
00:33:59,948 --> 00:34:03,111
Bless, dear Lord,
the food we take...

保佑，亲爱的主，我们吃的食物...

291
00:34:03,152 --> 00:34:04,642
and keep us all...

并让我们所有人...

292
00:34:06,021 --> 00:34:07,784
Oh, my God.

哦，我的上帝。

293
00:34:09,625 --> 00:34:14,324
And keep us all home and safe.

并让我们所有人安全回家。

294
00:34:14,363 --> 00:34:16,024
Amen.

阿门。

295
00:34:21,970 --> 00:34:22,959
Please start without me.

请你们先开始吃吧。

296
00:34:23,005 --> 00:34:23,994
I'll be right back.

我马上会回来。

297
00:34:30,312 --> 00:34:31,870
Braddock.

巴洛克。

298
00:34:31,914 --> 00:34:33,643
How on earth did you get here?

你到底是怎么到这里来的?

299
00:34:33,682 --> 00:34:34,649
Where's my wife?

我的妻子在哪儿？

300
00:34:34,683 --> 00:34:36,173
She doesn't live very far.

她住得并不是很远。

301
00:34:36,218 --> 00:34:37,651
Can you tell me
how to get there?

你能告诉我怎么到那儿吗？

302
00:34:37,686 --> 00:34:40,177
I'll take you there.

我会带你去那儿。

303
00:34:40,222 --> 00:34:44,158
Here. Wear this.
There's a curfew.

这里。戴上这顶。那边有一个宵禁。

304
00:34:44,193 --> 00:34:46,184
We must be very careful.

我们必须非常小心。

305
00:34:58,674 --> 00:35:01,165
I tried to tell you
how bad it was.

我尝试着告诉你那里有多恶劣。

306
00:35:02,377 --> 00:35:04,106
You'd better go, Reverend.

你最好还是离开，牧师。

307
00:35:04,146 --> 00:35:05,408
And thanks.

谢谢。

308
00:35:05,447 --> 00:35:08,143
Good luck. God bless you.

祝你好运。上帝保佑你。

309
00:36:44,746 --> 00:36:46,338
I didn't know.

我并不知道。

310
00:36:46,381 --> 00:36:47,678
I thought you were...

我以为你已经...

311
00:36:48,283 --> 00:36:50,547
It's not important.

这并不重要。

312
00:36:52,321 --> 00:36:55,017
I prayed you would
come for us...

我祈祷着你会为我们而来...

313
00:36:55,057 --> 00:36:56,922
and you are here.

然后你到这里了。

314
00:36:56,959 --> 00:36:59,951
That is all that matters
to Van and I.

这对凡和我来说才是最重要的。

315
00:37:05,467 --> 00:37:07,958
This is your son, Jim.

这是你的儿子，吉姆。

316
00:37:09,304 --> 00:37:10,566
Hello, Van.

你好，凡。

317
00:37:14,876 --> 00:37:16,901
I speak English, Braddock.

我会说英语，巴洛克。

318
00:37:19,815 --> 00:37:23,342
For years, he dreamed about you.

多年来，他都梦到你。

319
00:37:23,385 --> 00:37:26,821
Sometimes, in very
difficult moments...

有时候，在非常艰难的时刻...

320
00:37:26,855 --> 00:37:28,823
I would find him
talking to you...

我会找到他谈论你...

321
00:37:28,857 --> 00:37:30,324
as if you were there...

好像你就在那里...

322
00:37:30,359 --> 00:37:33,954
and somehow you would
make things right for him...

并且不论如何你都是做了对他有利的事情...

323
00:37:33,996 --> 00:37:37,830
but one day,
he stopped believing.

但是有一天，他不再相信。

324
00:37:37,866 --> 00:37:41,165
I tried to keep you
alive in his heart.

我尝试着让你活在他的心里。

325
00:37:42,004 --> 00:37:43,665
I tried.

我试过了。

326
00:37:52,914 --> 00:37:55,815
I guess I know
how you feel, Van...

我想我知道你的感受，凡...

327
00:37:56,952 --> 00:37:58,852
thinking that I deserted
you and your mother...

认为是我抛弃了你和你的妈妈...

328
00:37:58,887 --> 00:38:02,220
but... I want you
to know that...

但是...我想让你知道...

329
00:38:02,257 --> 00:38:04,191
Van, please.

凡，拜托。

330
00:38:05,327 --> 00:38:09,127
If I had known that you
and your mother were alive...

如果我早就知道你和你妈妈还活着...

331
00:38:10,632 --> 00:38:11,690
there's nothing in the world...

那么世界上就没有什么...

332
00:38:11,733 --> 00:38:14,634
that would have stopped me
from coming for you before now.

可以在此之前阻止我为你而来。

333
00:38:37,859 --> 00:38:39,486
You've suffered so much.

你已经受了那么多苦。

334
00:38:43,265 --> 00:38:46,132
I know I have changed, Jim.

我知道我已经变了，吉姆。

335
00:38:47,836 --> 00:38:52,102
I'm sorry I'm no longer
pretty for you.

很遗憾，对你来说我已经不再漂亮。

336
00:38:57,646 --> 00:39:00,479
You'll always be
beautiful to me.

对我而言你永远是最美丽的。

337
00:39:10,192 --> 00:39:11,784
We have to go now.

我们现在必须离开。

338
00:39:14,763 --> 00:39:16,128
We are ready.

我们都准备好了。

339
00:39:40,055 --> 00:39:42,148
Let me check the street first.

先让我查看一下街道。

340
00:40:30,772 --> 00:40:32,399
Van, hurry.

凡，快点。

341
00:41:26,795 --> 00:41:27,784
Come on.

来吧。

342
00:41:30,732 --> 00:41:32,199
Hurry, hurry.

快点，快点。

343
00:41:51,152 --> 00:41:53,279
The boat's right down there.

汽船就在那下面。

344
00:42:05,967 --> 00:42:07,161
It might be a tight squeeze...

也许会有点拥挤...

345
00:42:07,202 --> 00:42:09,602
but I think you're going
to enjoy the ride, Van.

但我认为你已经准备好享受航行了，凡。

346
00:42:09,638 --> 00:42:11,162
If you say so, Braddock.

如果你说是，那就是吧，巴洛克。

347
00:42:14,876 --> 00:42:16,503
Please be patient.

请耐心点。

348
00:42:16,544 --> 00:42:19,445
We've only had each other
for twelve years...

我们相依为命12年了...

349
00:42:19,481 --> 00:42:21,346
and now...

现在...

350
00:42:23,818 --> 00:42:26,787
it is very difficult for him.

对他而言很艰难。

351
00:42:27,489 --> 00:42:29,389
He will need some time.

他需要一些时间。

352
00:42:30,425 --> 00:42:32,222
We have all the time
in the world.

我们拥有世上的所有时间。

353
00:42:34,863 --> 00:42:37,957
I love you very much,
Jim Braddock.

我非常爱你，詹姆斯・巴洛克。

354
00:42:58,453 --> 00:43:01,980
I think I should talk
to our son for a moment.

我认为我应该和我们儿子谈一会儿。

355
00:43:02,023 --> 00:43:04,218
I'll go get the boat ready.

我去把船准备好。

356
00:43:10,532 --> 00:43:11,760
Van.

凡。

357
00:43:18,373 --> 00:43:20,534
Everything will be all right.

一切都会好起来的。

358
00:43:20,575 --> 00:43:22,509
You don't care about me now.

你现在不关心我了。

359
00:43:23,345 --> 00:43:24,539
You only care about HIM.

你只关心他！

360
00:43:24,579 --> 00:43:26,979
That is not true.

不是这样的。

361
00:43:27,015 --> 00:43:29,984
It was our love that
brought you into this world.

是我们的爱情让你诞生在这个世界上。

362
00:43:30,018 --> 00:43:32,578
Your father loves you as I do.

你父亲和我一样爱你。

363
00:43:32,620 --> 00:43:35,350
If you will only
give him a chance.

只要你给他一次机会。

364
00:43:35,390 --> 00:43:37,358
Please try, Van.

请尝试去做，凡。

365
00:43:53,041 --> 00:43:55,202
I'm very scared.

我很害怕。

366
00:43:57,779 --> 00:43:59,337
I know you are...

我都知道...

367
00:44:01,082 --> 00:44:02,811
but once we get to America...

但是一旦我们到了美国...

368
00:44:03,685 --> 00:44:05,346
everything will be better.

一切都会变得更好。

369
00:44:05,387 --> 00:44:06,820
I promise.

我发誓。

370
00:44:09,791 --> 00:44:12,885
Your father promises.

你爸爸也发誓。

371
00:44:12,927 --> 00:44:13,894
Lin, we have to
get out of here.

林，我们必须离开这里。

372
00:44:13,928 --> 00:44:14,917
Hurry!

赶快！

373
00:44:41,022 --> 00:44:42,455
Foolish.

愚蠢。

374
00:44:42,490 --> 00:44:43,957
You're in Nam.

你在越南。

375
00:44:45,660 --> 00:44:47,093
Very foolish to come back.

回来是相当愚蠢的。

376
00:44:47,128 --> 00:44:50,529
I am General Quoc.

我是阔克将军。

377
00:44:52,000 --> 00:44:55,492
How do you do, Madam Braddock?

你过得怎么样，巴洛克夫人？

378
00:44:55,537 --> 00:44:57,027
And yoi.

你呢。

379
00:44:58,840 --> 00:45:01,934
And this must be your son Van.

这一定是你的儿子凡。

380
00:45:01,976 --> 00:45:04,001
Very good-looking boy.

很帅气的男孩。

381
00:45:06,514 --> 00:45:09,039
When I received the report...

当我收到报告...

382
00:45:09,084 --> 00:45:12,520
that a strange-looking boat
had outrun my gunboats...

一艘外形奇特的船已经逃过我的炮艇...

383
00:45:12,554 --> 00:45:15,079
and heading towards
Ho Chi Minh city...

并朝着胡志明市而去...

384
00:45:15,123 --> 00:45:17,023
I took the privilege...

我假设...

385
00:45:17,058 --> 00:45:20,755
of assuming it was you,
Colonel Braddock...

那是你的特权,巴洛克上校...

386
00:45:20,795 --> 00:45:23,457
since Reverend Polanski
had just returned...

因为波兰斯基牧师刚刚返回...

387
00:45:23,498 --> 00:45:24,829
from your country...

自你们国家...

388
00:45:25,333 --> 00:45:26,994
but now...

但是现在...

389
00:45:28,236 --> 00:45:29,794
Braddock...

巴洛克...

390
00:45:31,473 --> 00:45:36,342
you must pay for the crimes
that you have committed...

你必须就致力于反对我所热爱的国家...

391
00:45:36,377 --> 00:45:38,777
against my beloved country.

而犯下的罪行付出代价。

392
00:45:38,813 --> 00:45:40,838
They have nothing
to do with this.

他们与此无关。

393
00:45:40,882 --> 00:45:45,182
You are absolutely right.

你绝对地正确。

394
00:45:52,494 --> 00:45:54,291
No!

不！

395
00:45:54,329 --> 00:45:58,356
Ma!

妈！

396
00:47:01,563 --> 00:47:03,997
You will find your first test...

你会发现 你第一项测试...

397
00:47:04,666 --> 00:47:06,463
quite challenging.

相当具有挑战性。

398
00:48:27,348 --> 00:48:30,749
Usually, we use people
who are...

通常，我们使用的人会...

399
00:48:30,785 --> 00:48:32,548
a little bit taller.

更高一点。

400
00:49:03,117 --> 00:49:05,813
I have tested
many before, Braddock...

我之前已经测试过很多了，巴洛克...

401
00:49:05,853 --> 00:49:09,755
and no one has lasted
even an hour.

并且没有人能坚持超过哪怕1个小时。

402
00:49:09,791 --> 00:49:12,988
Maybe you can be the first, eh?

你也许会成为第一个，额？

403
00:49:13,027 --> 00:49:14,892
I'll do whatever you want.

我会做任何你想要的。

404
00:49:15,630 --> 00:49:16,756
Just let the boy go.

只要你放走那个男孩。

405
00:49:20,101 --> 00:49:25,630
You will do what I want anyways.

不管怎样你都会做我想要的。

406
00:51:09,210 --> 00:51:10,199
Well done.

很好。

407
00:51:10,244 --> 00:51:12,769
Well done, Colonel Braddock.

非常好，巴洛克上校。

408
00:51:12,814 --> 00:51:16,580
You are every bit as tough
as your reputation.

你每一点都像你的声誉一样强硬。

409
00:51:17,351 --> 00:51:19,012
I like that.

我喜欢那样。

410
00:51:35,169 --> 00:51:37,831
You have not disappointed
me, Braddock.

你没有让我失望，巴洛克。

411
00:52:30,091 --> 00:52:31,080
No!

不！

412
00:52:38,061 --> 00:52:41,360
This has gone on long enough.

这已经持续了足够长的时间。

413
00:52:50,340 --> 00:52:52,103
No!

不！

414
00:55:47,951 --> 00:55:48,918
Van!

凡！

415
00:55:48,952 --> 00:55:50,647
I'm in here!

我在这里！

416
00:55:52,889 --> 00:55:53,878
Come on! Come on!

加油！加油！

417
00:56:33,263 --> 00:56:34,321
Can you make it?

你能做到吗？

418
00:56:34,364 --> 00:56:35,262
Yeah.

能。

419
00:56:35,298 --> 00:56:36,560
Go to the mission.

去教会。

420
00:59:16,125 --> 00:59:17,592
What's wrong?

怎么回事？

421
00:59:17,627 --> 00:59:18,616
What are you doing?

你们在干什么？

422
00:59:18,661 --> 00:59:20,993
Where is Braddock?

巴洛克在哪里？

423
00:59:23,299 --> 00:59:25,233
I don't know where
Braddock is, General.

我不知道巴洛克在哪里，将军。

424
00:59:25,268 --> 00:59:28,294
You lie, priest. You lie!

你在撒谎，牧师。你在撒谎！

425
00:59:28,338 --> 00:59:30,238
We know you helped Braddock!

我们知道你在帮助巴洛克！

426
00:59:30,273 --> 00:59:32,707
I? You must be mistaken.

我？你肯定是弄错了。

427
00:59:37,113 --> 00:59:38,080
You lie!

你在撒谎！

428
00:59:38,114 --> 00:59:41,481
Perhaps a change
of environment...

或许换一个环境...

429
00:59:41,517 --> 00:59:44,008
will help you
to think more clearly!

会帮你想地更清楚！

430
01:00:15,084 --> 01:00:16,142
Take him!

带走他！

431
01:00:19,188 --> 01:00:20,177
Please, no.

请求，别。

432
01:00:20,223 --> 01:00:21,212
I can't leave my children.

我不能离开我的孩子们。

433
01:00:21,257 --> 01:00:22,315
They need me!

他们需要我！

434
01:00:22,358 --> 01:00:24,519
Of course!

当然！

435
01:00:24,560 --> 01:00:26,187
I would not want
to separate you...

我不想把你...

436
01:00:26,229 --> 01:00:30,165
from your half-breed
American bastard children!

和你的混蛋半混血美国孩子们拆开！

437
01:00:31,034 --> 01:00:32,831
Take them all!

把所有人都带走！

438
01:01:46,642 --> 01:01:50,373
Priest, your new home
will be Olaha prison!

牧师，殴拉哈监狱将成为你们的新家！

439
01:07:06,629 --> 01:07:09,120
Don't! Don't!

不要！不要！

440
01:07:09,165 --> 01:07:10,154
Don't!

不要！

441
01:07:11,267 --> 01:07:15,135
No! No!

不！不！

442
01:07:40,663 --> 01:07:42,255
Stop!

停下！

443
01:07:46,368 --> 01:07:47,926
Stop!

停！

444
01:08:58,207 --> 01:08:59,799
Kids! In the truck!

孩子们！上卡车！

445
01:09:06,715 --> 01:09:07,773
Van!

凡！

446
01:09:07,816 --> 01:09:08,783
Where's the Reverend?

牧师在哪里？

447
01:09:08,817 --> 01:09:10,978
I know! I get him, Braddock!

我知道！我去找他，巴洛克！

448
01:10:48,183 --> 01:10:49,445
Come on, Reverend.

加油，牧师。

449
01:10:50,019 --> 01:10:51,782
Thank God, Braddock!

感谢上帝，巴洛克！

450
01:14:27,369 --> 01:14:28,768
Protect yourself!

保护好你们自己！

451
01:15:49,084 --> 01:15:51,314
Reverend, get the kids
out of here!

牧师，把孩子们从这里弄出去！

452
01:15:59,761 --> 01:16:02,286
Out! Hurry! Hurry!

出去！快点！快点！

453
01:16:02,331 --> 01:16:04,458
We must get away
from the truck!

我们必须远离卡车！

454
01:16:16,478 --> 01:16:18,708
Hurry up, Braddock! Here!

快点，巴洛克！这边！

455
01:16:44,039 --> 01:16:45,301
Get down, Reverend!

趴下，牧师！

456
01:17:22,110 --> 01:17:23,099
It's OK.

没事了。

457
01:17:32,654 --> 01:17:34,622
Ninety kilometers to the border.

距离边境90公里。

458
01:17:35,290 --> 01:17:36,814
You don't expect
these children...

你不是期望这些孩子们...

459
01:17:36,858 --> 01:17:38,519
to walk ninety kilometers!

步行90公里吧！

460
01:17:38,560 --> 01:17:40,721
I don't expect
a damn thing, Reverend.

我不期望一件该死的事情，牧师。

461
01:17:41,596 --> 01:17:44,895
But walk or crawl,
we're gonna make it.

但是不管走还是爬，我们必须做到。

462
01:17:44,933 --> 01:17:46,298
Come on, kids.

加油，孩子们。

463
01:17:53,608 --> 01:17:55,166
Come on, Reverend.

加油，牧师。

464
01:18:24,072 --> 01:18:25,164
Braddock...

巴洛克...

465
01:18:26,074 --> 01:18:27,098
Braddock...

巴洛克...

466
01:18:31,079 --> 01:18:32,944
the children are dead tired.

孩子们累得要命。

467
01:18:32,981 --> 01:18:34,539
We must stop to rest.

你必须停下来休息。

468
01:18:34,583 --> 01:18:37,051
Please, Braddock.

拜托，巴洛克。

469
01:18:37,085 --> 01:18:38,950
They are not very strong.

他们不是很强壮。

470
01:18:50,198 --> 01:18:51,859
Wait here.

在这里等着。

471
01:19:39,514 --> 01:19:41,311
Reverend. Reverend!

牧师。牧师！

472
01:19:41,349 --> 01:19:42,611
Bring the kids.

把孩子们带来。

473
01:19:42,651 --> 01:19:43,743
Hurry.

赶快。

474
01:19:43,785 --> 01:19:45,184
Come. Come, children.

来吧。来，孩子们。

475
01:19:45,220 --> 01:19:47,484
Quiet. Be quiet.

安静。保持安静。

476
01:22:12,300 --> 01:22:15,133
Come, children. Hurry. Hurry.

来，孩子们。快。快。

477
01:22:19,007 --> 01:22:20,872
Come, children.

来吧，孩子们。

478
01:22:20,909 --> 01:22:23,377
Be careful. Be careful.
Don't hurt yourselves.

小心。小心。别伤着自己。

479
01:22:25,213 --> 01:22:26,373
Come.

来。

480
01:22:27,716 --> 01:22:28,808
Go. Go.

走。走。

481
01:22:42,831 --> 01:22:44,856
Come on, kids. Hurry!

加油，孩子们。快点！

482
01:22:52,173 --> 01:22:55,165
Hurry! Hurry! Hurry up!

快点！快点！赶快！

483
01:23:04,085 --> 01:23:05,575
Thomas!

托马斯！

484
01:23:13,962 --> 01:23:14,951
Hurry!

快点！

485
01:23:30,211 --> 01:23:32,372
Sit down and hold on.

坐下，抓稳。

486
01:23:37,719 --> 01:23:38,708
Damn it.

该死的。

487
01:24:11,986 --> 01:24:14,853
Braddock, get back, you bastard!

巴洛克，回来，你这个杂种！

488
01:24:16,191 --> 01:24:18,352
Come on!

来吧！

489
01:24:21,696 --> 01:24:23,857
Hold on!

抓稳！

490
01:24:33,975 --> 01:24:36,068
Braddock! I will kill you...

巴洛克！我会杀了你...

491
01:24:36,110 --> 01:24:38,943
and I will burn
those filthy children!

还会烧死那些肮脏的孩子们！

492
01:24:54,996 --> 01:24:56,486
Hold on.

抓稳。

493
01:25:02,070 --> 01:25:04,368
Oh, my God.

哦，我的上帝。

494
01:25:05,373 --> 01:25:07,000
Get back there
with the kids, Reverend.

回到孩子们中去，牧师。

495
01:25:09,644 --> 01:25:11,509
It's gonna get rough.

马上要变艰难。

496
01:25:15,550 --> 01:25:18,018
It's going to get rough.

正在变地艰难。

497
01:25:43,344 --> 01:25:45,437
Mayday. Mayday.

呼救。呼救。

498
01:25:46,948 --> 01:25:48,472
This is
Colonel James Braddock...

这里是巴洛克上校...

499
01:25:48,516 --> 01:25:51,781
calling American Military
Assistance Command.

呼叫美国军事援助指挥部。

500
01:25:51,819 --> 01:25:53,184
Come in.

进来。

501
01:25:53,221 --> 01:25:54,745
Mayday. Mayday.

呼救。呼救。

502
01:25:56,524 --> 01:25:58,788
Here. Take a seat.

这里，坐下。

503
01:25:59,794 --> 01:26:01,455
Mayday. Mayday.

呼救。呼救。

504
01:26:01,496 --> 01:26:03,157
This is Colonel Braddock.

这里是巴洛克上校。

505
01:26:03,197 --> 01:26:05,791
I'm in a crippled C-47.

我在一架受损的C-47上。

506
01:26:05,833 --> 01:26:08,427
I have a planeload
of Amerasian children.

我有整整一飞机的美亚混血儿童。

507
01:26:08,469 --> 01:26:09,697
Losing fuel.

正在漏油。

508
01:26:09,737 --> 01:26:13,400
I'm approximately eight miles
east of the Thai border.

我大约在泰国边境以东8英里处。【1英里=1.6公里】

509
01:26:13,441 --> 01:26:16,535
If anyone can hear me,
please transfer this message...

如果任何人能听到我，请把这条信息转发...

510
01:26:16,578 --> 01:26:19,308
to the American Military
Assistance Command.

给美国军事援助指挥部。

511
01:26:20,048 --> 01:26:22,107
Is everyone OK back there?

那边每个人都还好吗？

512
01:26:23,718 --> 01:26:25,242
Are you OK?

你还好吗？

513
01:26:25,286 --> 01:26:27,186
Yeah. I fine.

是的。我很好。

514
01:26:27,221 --> 01:26:28,313
How you?

你怎样？

515
01:26:28,356 --> 01:26:29,687
I'm fine, too.

我也很好。

516
01:26:55,917 --> 01:26:58,044
Reverend! We're going down!

牧师！我们在坠落！

517
01:26:58,086 --> 01:27:00,247
Children! Get down!

孩子们！趴下！

518
01:27:00,288 --> 01:27:02,779
Hold on! Hold on!

坚持住！坚持住！

519
01:27:12,634 --> 01:27:13,965
We're gonna die!

我们会死！

520
01:27:14,002 --> 01:27:15,799
Just hold on!

只要坚持住！

521
01:27:49,537 --> 01:27:50,868
Van.

凡。

522
01:28:11,225 --> 01:28:12,453
Come on, Van.

来吧，凡。

523
01:28:14,195 --> 01:28:15,890
Help the kids.

帮助孩子们。

524
01:29:10,718 --> 01:29:12,379
Everybody down.

全都趴下。

525
01:29:12,420 --> 01:29:13,751
Reverend.

牧师。

526
01:29:17,892 --> 01:29:19,655
My God.

我的上帝！

527
01:29:19,694 --> 01:29:22,561
Braddock, there's the border.

巴洛克，那边就是边境。

528
01:29:23,064 --> 01:29:24,793
As soon as I take
the guards out...

一旦我除去守卫们...

529
01:29:24,832 --> 01:29:26,800
you get the kids
over the bridge...

你就带孩子们过桥...

530
01:29:26,834 --> 01:29:27,994
as fast as you can.

越快越好。

531
01:29:30,271 --> 01:29:31,738
Did you hear what I said?

你听到我说的了吗？

532
01:30:02,436 --> 01:30:04,734
On my way over here...

来这里的路上...

533
01:30:04,772 --> 01:30:06,831
I was wondering
what you would be like.

我很疑惑你会是什么样子。

534
01:30:06,874 --> 01:30:08,637
I want you to know...

我想让你知道...

535
01:30:08,676 --> 01:30:10,940
you're everything
I wanted in a son...

你是我期待的那个好儿子...

536
01:30:12,413 --> 01:30:14,278
and I'm very proud of you.

我为你感到非常骄傲。

537
01:30:23,524 --> 01:30:24,991
I love you.

我爱你。

538
01:31:10,605 --> 01:31:12,835
All right, men. Let's go.

好了，伙计们。出发。

539
01:31:14,108 --> 01:31:16,338
What the hell is happening, Dan?

那边正在发生什么鬼事情，丹？

540
01:31:16,377 --> 01:31:17,469
Braddock and the children.

巴洛克和孩子们。

541
01:31:17,511 --> 01:31:19,342
We intercepted a radio message.

我们收到一条无线电信息。

542
01:31:19,380 --> 01:31:21,678
They crashed
somewhere near here.

他们在这附近坠机。

543
01:32:23,444 --> 01:32:25,674
Oh, shit.

哦，见鬼。

544
01:32:52,673 --> 01:32:54,300
Van!

凡！

545
01:33:08,723 --> 01:33:09,712
Don't go!

别去！

546
01:33:10,758 --> 01:33:12,089
Can't leave him, Dan.

不能离开他，丹。

547
01:33:12,126 --> 01:33:13,093
I got to help him.

我要去帮他。

548
01:33:13,127 --> 01:33:15,027
Leave it alone, General.
He's on his own.

让他一个人战斗，将军。他只能靠自己。

549
01:33:15,062 --> 01:33:17,030
No one crosses the border.

没人可以穿越边境。

550
01:33:30,711 --> 01:33:32,906
Get a medic in, man.

找一个医生进去，伙计。

551
01:33:43,691 --> 01:33:44,680
All right!

好的！

552
01:34:08,382 --> 01:34:09,349
Daddy!

爸爸！

553
01:34:09,383 --> 01:34:10,941
Don't go!

别过去！

554
01:34:14,855 --> 01:34:16,254
Christ.

老天。【基督】

555
01:34:41,215 --> 01:34:43,115
I got you, Braddock!

我逮到你了，巴洛克！

556
01:34:43,150 --> 01:34:44,447
I got you!

我逮到你了！

557
01:34:44,485 --> 01:34:45,679
Daddy!

爸爸！

558
01:34:45,719 --> 01:34:48,187
No, no. No, Van.
Get back! Get back!

不，不。不，凡。退后！退后！

559
01:34:48,222 --> 01:34:49,246
No. No. Please!

不。不。拜托！

560
01:34:52,993 --> 01:34:54,426
You're finished, Braddock!

你完蛋了，巴洛克！

561
01:34:54,462 --> 01:34:56,089
I've won!

我赢了！

562
01:35:10,411 --> 01:35:13,778
They will not dare to cross.

他们不敢穿越。

563
01:35:27,862 --> 01:35:29,454
What's he doing?

他在干什么？

564
01:35:35,469 --> 01:35:37,699
Hold your position.

保持你的位置.

565
01:35:39,874 --> 01:35:43,810
He makes one wrong move,we'll climb up his ass.

